(171, 'wpb_js_templates', 'a:4:{s:27:"portfolio-top-page_41389211";a:2:{s:4:"name";s:18:"Portfolio Top Page";s:8:"template";s:496:"[vc_row][vc_column width="1/1"][background_block bgimage="16" bgcolor="#000000" opacity="0.85" contentcolorclass="light-on-dark" parallax="enabled" parspeed="8" ptop="20" btwidth="0" btcolor="#44576a" bbwidth="0" bbcolor="#44576a"][vc_column_text css_animation="appear"]\n<h1 style="text-align: center;">Meet the dogs</h1>\n<p style="text-align: center;">(Click the links to filter)</p>\n\n[/vc_column_text][spacer height="35"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/1"][/vc_column][/vc_row]";}s:18:"catpage_1287005455";a:2:{s:4:"name";s:7:"catpage";s:8:"template";s:692:"[vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="205" css_animation="left-to-right" img_link_large="yes" img_link_target="_self" img_size="large"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]This is Mr Castor.\n\nHe currently resides in the house at Crimea Cottage and has been with us since XXXX.\n\nIf you would like to sponsor Mr Castor please get in touch.[/vc_column_text][vc_cta_button call_text="If you would like to adopt, sponsor or have any questions, please do get in touch. " title="Contact Us" target="_self" color="btn-primary" icon="none" size="btn-large" position="cta_align_bottom" href="http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/get-in-touch/"][/vc_column][/vc_row]";}s:19:"dog-page_1143605304";a:2:{s:4:"name";s:8:"Dog Page";s:8:"template";s:675:"[vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="59" border_color="grey" img_link_large="yes" img_link_target="_self" img_size="large"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]This is lance and he was born in 2006.\n\nHe has been a racing dog and now would like to retire on to your sofa and make you a good pet and companion.[/vc_column_text][vc_cta_button2 h2="To arrange a visit, adopt or sponsor, please do get in touch. " style="rounded" txt_align="left" title="Contact Us" btn_style="rounded" color="blue" size="md" position="bottom" link="url:http%3A%2F%2Fwww.greyhoundrescue.org.uk%2F2014site%2Fget-in-touch%2F|title:Contact%20Us|"][/vc_column][/vc_row]";}s:37:"wolfies-breeze-block-appeal_431155775";a:2:{s:4:"name";s:28:"Wolfie''s Breeze Block Appeal";s:8:"template";s:1504:"<strong>Wolfie’s Breeze Block Appeal</strong>\n\n<strong>Greyhound Rescue have planned to build an extension to help other people when they find it impossible to contemplate a holiday because they simply do not want their pets to be put in a kennel environment.</strong>\n\n<strong>So, this extension will give peoples pets a home from home environment, with live in humans to see to their every needs, whilst their owners can go and enjoy their well earned holiday with peace of mind that their pets are in good hands.</strong>\n\n<strong>This decision was also brought forward because of unforeseen circumstances of owners needing to go into hospital for a length a time and we have been in the position of having to put their pets into the kennels. This has been quite upsetting in the past and distressing for the pets.</strong>\n\n<strong>We have thought long and hard about this and how we can help owners and their pets and with this in mind, we have decided to run a breeze block appeal to help with the funding of our project.</strong>\n\n<strong>This will be called, <em>‘Wolfie’s Breeze Block Appeal’</em>. This is in memory of our beautiful blue girl Wolfie who we lost late last year at the grand young age of 22.</strong>\n\n<strong>Wolfie was an amazing greyhound and was at the rescue for 20 years. We will be sharing her story and pictures throughout the appeal.</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong>Thank you.</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong>Karen Schultz (&amp; Wolfie) X</strong>";}}', 'yes'),
