(26, 1, '2014-03-02 21:20:05', '2014-03-02 21:20:05', '[vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="400" border_color="grey" img_link_large="yes" img_link_target="_self" img_size="large"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]<span style="line-height: 107%; font-family: ''Gungsuh'',serif; font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: #000000;"> </span></span>\r\n\r\nWell. What can I say? Here we have Buster! He is a fawn male greyhound of 5 years old. He has been with us at greyhound rescue for nearly a year now, through no fault of his own.\r\n\r\nWe have had many enquiries about him but he was on reserve for quite some time for one couple who seemed the right choice. We kept him on reserve as promised for them but unfortunately their house sale fell through and circumstances changed for them and it just wasn’t to be for Buster. This does mean that Buster has been here far longer than he should have been as he is a fantastic dog.\r\n\r\nNow, let me tell you about him. He is a fairly big lad and very friendly. He is extremely clean in his kennel and a kind soul.\r\n\r\nHe is a strong boy and fussy on meeting him but calms down very quickly. He can jump up occasionally on first meeting but just to give you a friendly hello! He can also be quite shy when he first meets people but soon overcomes this.\r\n\r\nBuster loves to play and has a realy friendly nature. He’s just a big baby really!\r\n\r\nAll the female greyhounds fancy Buster and so the very sight of him causes havoc with our girls! So, whoever gets to re-home him, will have to watch out as he is quite the handsome guy! Likes to keep himself looking good for the ladies! They will be knocking at your door to meet him!\r\n\r\nHe is a gentle guy and very loving. Have to say, when he does go, I will miss him but I do want him to find someone special and that sofa to lay on and the love and attention he deserves, one to one.\r\n\r\nThis boy is very special, very kind, funny and one of the nicest greyhounds you will meet.\r\n\r\nHe loves his food and chews and as much fuss and cuddles as you can give him.\r\n\r\nWhilst Buster does get on with other dogs he does need a home with no other pets and preferably older children if any.\r\n\r\nIf you think you may be the right human for Buster then please give me a call on 01205 290145 or 07811 296029.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThank you\r\n\r\nDawn\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_cta_button2 h2="To arrange a visit, adopt or sponsor, please do get in touch. " style="rounded" txt_align="left" title="Contact Us" btn_style="rounded" color="blue" size="md" position="bottom" link="url:http%3A%2F%2Fwww.greyhoundrescue.org.uk%2F2014site%2Fget-in-touch%2F|title:Contact%20Us|"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="59" border_color="grey" img_link_large="yes" img_link_target="_self" img_size="large"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]This is lance and he was born in 2006.\r\n\r\nHe has been a racing dog and now would like to retire on to your sofa and make you a good pet and companion.[/vc_column_text][vc_cta_button2 h2="To arrange a visit, adopt or sponsor, please do get in touch. " style="rounded" txt_align="left" title="Contact Us" btn_style="rounded" color="blue" size="md" position="bottom" link="url:http%3A%2F%2Fwww.greyhoundrescue.org.uk%2F2014site%2Fget-in-touch%2F|title:Contact%20Us|"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Buster - Urgent Appeal', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'buster', '', '', '2015-01-15 15:56:28', '2015-01-15 15:56:28', '', 0, 'http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/?post_type=thedogs&#038;p=26', 0, 'thedogs', '', 0),
