(90, 1, '2014-04-21 19:25:14', '2014-04-21 19:25:14', '[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]Owners have raced greyhounds for many years and race goers see them muzzled, chasing a make believe hare. The public gain a lot of excitement from the spectacle and gamble thousands of pounds on their performance. When they have finished their usual track life, either because they are too old, injured, or just not fast enough, they are disposed of. The luck ones end up in Greyhound Rescue for re-homing as family pets.\r\n\r\nThe problem they then have is overcoming the public''s image of the breed. It is generally thought that they need to be kept muzzled, are dangerous around children and need lots of exercise.\r\n\r\nAs with all breeds each greyhound has it''s own temperament but in general greyhounds are extremely lazy, spending most of their time either flat on their backs, with their legs in the air, or sprawled out in their bed fast asleep. Most only need two walks a day and the freedom of an enclosed back garden. They love a cuddle and in particular like their bellies rubbed.\r\n\r\nA greyhound sees a lot further than a human being and if they see something in the distance they will set off to chase it, so it is wise to keep them on a lead at all times when walking them, but they saunter along at a genteel pace, giving the owners a steady walk.\r\n\r\nIn general a Greyhound is one of the most loving pets to own and will give many years of love and friendship to it''s lucky owner.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/1"][vc_cta_button call_text="If you are interested in learning more about greyhounds, please ask us anything and we''ll do our best to help. " title="Get In Touch" target="_self" color="btn-primary" icon="wpb_arrow" size="wpb_regularsize" position="cta_align_right"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'About Greyhounds', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '89-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-21 19:25:14', '2014-04-21 19:25:14', '', 89, 'http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/89-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(65, 1, '2014-03-02 23:42:40', '2014-03-02 23:42:40', '[vc_row][vc_column width="1/1"][vc_column_text]We are a charity based in Lincolnshire and Yorkshire and have spent over 25 years caring for and helping re-home these kind, gentle, affectionate and appreciative breed.[/vc_column_text][vc_separator][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/4"][service_block title="Adopt" target="_self" icon="icon-heart-1"]If you have a loving home and are ready for the love a greyhound will give, please get in touch.[/service_block][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][service_block title="Sponsor" icon="icon-heart-1" href="#" target="_self"]If you can''t give a dog a home but want to help, you can sponsor one of our dogs - they''ll love you for it![/service_block][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][service_block title="Donate" icon="icon-heart-1" target="_self"]If you just want to help retired and abandoned greyhounds with a donation, you can do that with paypal. Thanks![/service_block][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][service_block title="Shop" icon="icon-basket-1" target="_self"]We have calendars and other items for sale in the on-line shop. All proceeds go straight to the welfare of the dogs.[/service_block][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/1"][velocity_headline title="Meet the Dogs" target="_self"][latest_projects portfolio="thedogs" columns="5" items="8" height="225"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '12-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-02 23:42:40', '2014-03-02 23:42:40', '', 12, 'http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/12-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
