(68, 1, '2014-03-02 23:59:00', '2014-03-02 23:59:00', 'On 25th August 2013 we are doing a calendar photoshoot for our 2014 Greyhound Rescue calendar in aid of ''The Rescue Duke Appeal''!\r\nThanks to the boys at Kennings Building Supplies Ltd/eDecks &amp; some local girls who have kindly donated their bodies to raise money and awareness for our charity.\r\nWe would like to thank Kennings Building Supplies Ltd/eDecks staff who are taking part in the calendar and Nigel and Michaela Kenning for the use of a few tools.\r\nNo way to talk about their staff I know but I am sure it will be a lot of fun and I can confirm that Karen Schultz, much to her horror is also appearing in the calendar and I can assure you, she will be removing some items of clothing. However, I have been told she would have to have her wellies surgically removed so due to timescales, they may have to stay on!\r\nPlease watch out for more updates on the calendar in the next few days.\r\n\r\nThe Calendars are now on sale at £5.99 plus postage (no more than £1.00).\r\n\r\nPlease look at our lastest news content to see more on calendars.\r\n\r\nThank you\r\nDawn', 'Calender Photoshoot!', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-02 23:59:00', '2014-03-02 23:59:00', '', 1, 'http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/1-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(89, 1, '2014-04-21 19:26:23', '2014-04-21 19:26:23', '[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]Owners have raced greyhounds for many years and race goers see them muzzled, chasing a make believe hare. The public gain a lot of excitement from the spectacle and gamble thousands of pounds on their performance. When they have finished their usual track life, either because they are too old, injured, or just not fast enough, they are disposed of. The lucky ones end up in Greyhound Rescue for re-homing as family pets.\r\n\r\nThe problem they then have is overcoming the public''s image of the breed. It is generally thought that they need to be kept muzzled, are dangerous around children and need lots of exercise.\r\n\r\nAs with all breeds each greyhound has it''s own temperament but in general greyhounds are extremely lazy, spending most of their time either flat on their backs, with their legs in the air, or sprawled out in their bed fast asleep. Most only need two walks a day and the freedom of an enclosed back garden. They love a cuddle and in particular like their bellies rubbed.\r\n\r\nA greyhound sees a lot further than a human being and if they see something in the distance they will set off to chase it, so it is wise to keep them on a lead at all times when walking them, but they saunter along at a genteel pace, giving the owners a steady walk.\r\n\r\nIn general a Greyhound is one of the most loving pets to own and will give many years of love and friendship to it''s lucky owner.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/1"][vc_cta_button call_text="If you are interested in learning more about greyhounds, please ask us anything and we''ll do our best to help. " title="Get In Touch" target="_self" color="btn-primary" icon="wpb_arrow" size="wpb_regularsize" position="cta_align_right"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'About Greyhounds', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'about-greyhounds', '', '', '2014-12-30 17:39:38', '2014-12-30 17:39:38', '', 0, 'http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/?page_id=89', 0, 'page', '', 0),
