(419, 1, '2014-11-03 16:50:00', '2014-11-03 16:50:00', '[vc_row][vc_column width="1/1"][vc_column_text]I first met Gamble in 2005 when Karen introduced me to him and within hours he became the love of my life....as all greyhounds do. He was such a big strong sloppy clown. A very playful boy who I will adore until forever. I lost him on the 2nd November 2011 and it is a day although I wish I could block out of my mind, I know I never will. He died in my arms at 3.45am. He should not have gone at that time and was due to a dental.\r\n\r\nMe, Beau &amp; Karen miss you so much my boy but I know you are here with me even though I cannot feel you physically.\r\n\r\nI will never say goodbye, only goodnight young man. xxxx\r\n\r\nMummy[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Gamble', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '415-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-11-03 16:50:00', '2014-11-03 16:50:00', '', 415, 'http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/415-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
