 been happiness, frustration, sadness and all those other emotions running riot that form part of running an animal sanctuary, but most of all there has been the feeling of great satisfaction when a greyhound has been re-homed into a loving family life, a life that enables them to build their own character, to be an individual and at last find themselves belonging and loved by someone special.\r\n\r\nGreyhounds are great characters and dare we say it, have a great sense of humour. (We''re just waiting for scientists to finally catch up with what all Greyhound owners already know!)[/vc_column_text][spacer height="25"][velocity_headline title="Meet the Dogs" target="_self"][latest_projects portfolio="thedogs" columns="5" items="8" height="225"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '12-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-17 21:05:41', '2014-09-17 21:05:41', '', 12, 'http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/12-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
