(174, 3, '2014-09-19 21:39:35', '2014-09-19 21:39:35', '[vc_row][vc_column width="1/1"][vc_column_text]We are a charity based in Lincolnshire and Yorkshire and have spent over 25 years caring for and helping re-home these kind, gentle, affectionate and appreciative breed.[/vc_column_text][vc_separator][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/4"][service_block title="Adopt" target="_self" icon="icon-heart-1" href="http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/meet-the-dogs/"]If you have a loving home and are ready for the love a greyhound will give, please get in touch.[/service_block][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][service_block title="Sponsor" icon="icon-heart-1" href="http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/meet-the-dogs/" target="_self"]If you can''t give a dog a home but want to help, you can sponsor one of our dogs - they''ll love you for it![/service_block][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][service_block title="Donate" icon="icon-heart-1" target="_blank" href="https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr?cmd=_s-xclick&amp;hosted_button_id=5E7JL56V28B2C"]If you just want to help retired and abandoned greyhounds with a donation, you can do that with paypal. Thanks![/service_block][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][service_block title="Shop" icon="icon-basket-1" target="_self" href="http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/shop/"]We have calendars and other items for sale in the on-line shop. All proceeds go straight to the welfare of the dogs.[/service_block][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/1"][vc_column_text]Many of you will know the story of our chairpersons first sighting of two greyhounds, she was aged ten, yet the elegance and beauty of the breed lived with her until the age of 23 when she was able to adopt a greyhound of her own. From there a great passion for these noble gentle dogs was built and so the rescue sanctuary began.\r\n\r\nLooking back over the years we have helped greyhounds from many different circumstances. There has been happiness, frustration, sadness and all those other emotions running riot that form part of running an animal sanctuary, but most of all there has been the feeling of great satisfaction when a greyhound has been re-homed into a loving family life, a life that enables them to build their own character, to be an individual and at last find themselves belonging and loved by someone special.\r\n\r\nGreyhounds are great characters and dare we say it, have a great sense of humour. (We''re just waiting for scientists to finally catch up with what all Greyhound owners already know!)[/vc_column_text][spacer height="25"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][velocity_headline title="Sponsor a Dog" target="_self"][vc_column_text]<img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-173" src="http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/tommycrop_tall-217x300.jpg" alt="tommycrop_tall" width="217" height="300" />In addition to rehoming greyhounds, we also offer sponsorships.Unfortunately, some of the dogs that are with us have suffered severe trauma and will probably never be able to be re-homed.However, you can help by sponsoring. We will keep you updated with photographs, newsletters and a Christmas card! Please see how you can sponsor a dog in the information section.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][velocity_headline title="Sponsor a Cat. (Yes, really!)" target="_self"][vc_column_text]<img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-171" src="http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Mr_Castor-225x300.jpg" alt="Mr_Castor" width="225" height="300" />Having over the last couple of years, (and somewhat surprisingly) found ourselves a meeting place for stray cats, we now have a number of permanent residents that may not at first seem congruent with a Greyhound Rescue, but we never turn a homeless animal away.\r\nWe now have a dozen cats that could use your help via sponsorship or donation and we hope soon, to help them into new homes.\r\nThe chap to the left goes by the name of Mr Castor and was a great friend of our now departed beautiful girl Wolfie.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '12-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-19 21:39:35', '2014-09-19 21:39:35', '', 12, 'http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/12-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
