(273, 3, '2014-09-22 18:16:14', '2014-09-22 18:16:14', '[vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="29" border_color="grey" img_link_large="yes" img_link_target="_self" img_size="large"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]This is lance and he was born in 2006.\n\nHe has been a racing dog and now would like to retire on to your sofa and make you a good pet and companion.[/vc_column_text][vc_cta_button2 h2="To arrange a visit, adopt or sponsor, please do get in touch. " style="rounded" txt_align="left" title="Contact Us" btn_style="rounded" color="blue" size="md" position="bottom" link="url:http%3A%2F%2Fwww.greyhoundrescue.org.uk%2F2014site%2Fget-in-touch%2F|title:Contact%20Us|"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'George', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '28-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-09-22 18:16:14', '2014-09-22 18:16:14', '', 28, 'http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/28-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(274, 3, '2014-09-22 18:18:35', '2014-09-22 18:18:35', '[vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="27" border_color="grey" img_link_large="yes" img_link_target="_self" img_size="large"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]Buster is a beautiful fawn male.\r\n\r\nHe has a big heart and loves cuddles. He loves to play and has a real friendly nature.\r\n\r\nHe enjoys his walks and never leaves your side.\r\n\r\nBuster will make a real companion.\r\n\r\nHe is a very fussy boy and loves people and although he does get on with other dogs we would say that Buster would be better off as an only dog as he does need one to one attention and needs someone who understands greyhounds as he can be a little giddy at times.\r\n\r\nHaving said this he can also be quite shy to start with and does have a lot to say for himself when the other dogs are around.\r\n\r\nHe is a very friendly boy and a big baby!\r\n\r\nWe would recommend that Buster be rehomed with no other pets and no young children.[/vc_column_text][vc_cta_button2 h2="To arrange a visit, adopt or sponsor, please do get in touch. " style="rounded" txt_align="left" title="Contact Us" btn_style="rounded" color="blue" size="md" position="bottom" link="url:http%3A%2F%2Fwww.greyhoundrescue.org.uk%2F2014site%2Fget-in-touch%2F|title:Contact%20Us|"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Buster', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '26-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-09-22 18:18:35', '2014-09-22 18:18:35', '', 26, 'http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/26-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(276, 3, '2014-09-22 18:27:59', '2014-09-22 18:27:59', '[vc_row][vc_column width="1/1"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h1 style="text-align: center;">In Memorium</h1>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="213" alignment="center" img_link_target="_self" img_size="full"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h3>Kenny &amp; Archie</h3>\r\nIt is with such massive heartache to let our rescue friends and sponsors know that we have had to say goodbye to 2 of our most precious boys.\r\nKenny &amp; Archie both fell asleep this morning 8th August 2014 at the age of 19.\r\nThey had been with Karen here at the rescue for over 15 years as they could not be rehomed due to the horrific traumas they had suffered in their racing days.\r\nBoth Kenny &amp; Archie were brilliant dogs and gentle, brave boys until the end.\r\nWe will miss you always boys and the kennels will never be the same without you. xxxxx\r\n\r\nAll our love forever\r\nKaren &amp; Dawn[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="214" alignment="center" img_link_target="_self" img_size="full"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h3>Duke</h3>\r\nIt is with sadness and regret that we have to announce the loss of Duke who sadly passed away on Monday 25th March 2013.\r\nTo all his friends and the people who loved him\r\nThose who knew him so well and those who he made laugh\r\nAll the hearts he touched with his brave and determined willpower\r\nNever complaining about anything, even though he was not only blind but he had so many other problems.\r\nHis character of fun and joy won everyone’s affection, who were lucky enough to meet him.\r\nFor this beautiful black greyhound''s soul, so precious to us, so special and loving.\r\nHe has now left us, so quickly and suddenly, and broken so many hearts.\r\nWe have lost a dear friend in you, young man and a hole in our lives.\r\n\r\nThere will never be another ‘Duke’ X\r\n\r\nKaren Schultz…. (Duke’s mum).[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_single_image image="64" border_color="grey" img_link_target="_self"][/vc_column][vc_column width="3/4"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h3>Wolfie</h3>\r\nIt is with great sadness that we have to tell you that we have now lost wolfie. She passed away after a short illness and has left a massive hole in our lives. She was 20 years old though had the body and energy of a puppy, right until the end.\r\n\r\nWolfie had the most horrendous start to her life and it took Karen some time to win Wolfie round as she was so terrified of everyone. I, as well as everyone who met ''The Wolf'' will miss her forever. She was one of a kind and she was a kind girl. Patch and West have lost their sister and I know the Wolf missed Queenie her Bengal friend who we lost a few months ago. She has now joined her. Whitey, the cat and Caster the new Bengal will also miss her. She adored the cats as they did her.\r\n\r\nLove always our Angel. xxxxx\r\n\r\nMummy and Dawn\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI am Wolfie. I am a beautiful tiny blue greyhound who loves to sing! I am an old lady and my singing voice is not what it used to be...or so Patch tells me.\r\n\r\nMe &amp; Patch are best of friends though and love to cuddle up together on a night.\r\n\r\nMy mum Karen adores my singing as I do hers! (NOT)! I often pretend to not hear mum when she calls me in from the garden. She thinks my sight &amp; hearing is going as I am so old but I still enjoy my food and a good old dance around the kitchen table with Queenie the house cat.\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'In Memorium ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '212-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-22 18:27:59', '2014-09-22 18:27:59', '', 212, 'http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/212-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(277, 3, '2014-09-22 18:43:43', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '[vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="59" border_color="grey" img_link_large="yes" img_link_target="_self" img_size="large"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]This is lance and he was born in 2006.\n\nHe has been a racing dog and now would like to retire on to your sofa and make you a good pet and companion.[/vc_column_text][vc_cta_button2 h2="To arrange a visit, adopt or sponsor, please do get in touch. " style="rounded" txt_align="left" title="Contact Us" btn_style="rounded" color="blue" size="md" position="bottom" link="url:http%3A%2F%2Fwww.greyhoundrescue.org.uk%2F2014site%2Fget-in-touch%2F|title:Contact%20Us|"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', '', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2014-09-22 18:43:43', '2014-09-22 18:43:43', '', 0, 'http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/?post_type=thedogs&#038;p=277', 0, 'thedogs', '', 0),
(411, 1, '2014-11-03 16:31:27', '2014-11-03 16:31:27', '[vc_row][vc_column width="1/1"][vc_column_text]Please watch panorama - Exposing Greyhound Racing. Undercover investigation into the devastation behind the scenes of Greyhound Racing &amp; the thounsand of greyhounds that disappear each year.\r\n\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAn update on this Panorama investigation - Our view from Greyhound Rescue!\r\n\r\nAll this program served to do is to give GBGB the chance to continue to self regulate and let this man get a slap on the wrist. The program in no way showed the injuries these greyhounds get on the track, nor did it show the fact these dogs are raced whilst injured &amp; put to sleep for no valid reason etc. It did not speak up about the true facts of the dogs that go missing each year, nor did it investigate any of the abuse that these dogs suffer. It did not go into what happens to the dogs that do not make the grade or when they are retired.\r\n\r\nWe as a rescue only get a fraction of the ''lucky ones'' if that is what you can call them and many cannot be re-homed because of the abuse they have suffered.\r\n\r\nAll this program was about was race fixing, doping and money. Well, this is all history, nothing new and has been going on years. It also really only focused on one trainer - well, there are many who do this and many who abuse greyhounds. BUT.... more than the trainers, we should really be looking at the OWNERS! These are the ones that OWN the greyhounds and who the trainers are working for. The Owners should be made accountable.\r\n\r\nThere may be some bad trainers but focus on the bad owners.\r\n\r\nNobody gave a voice to those dogs in my opinion - it was. The World needs to open its eyes and do something. The government needs to do something. NOW.\r\n\r\nWe stare into their eyes each day. We have seen their pain.\r\n\r\nPlease watch the 2 videos that were on tv from a few years ago on our website - all that needs to be added is 2009, 2010, 2011, 2012. 1213, 2014 NOTHING HAS CHANGED!!![/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Panorama documentary BBC1 8.30pm Monday 3rd November 2014', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'panorama-documentary-bbc1-8-30pm-monday-3rd-november-2014', '', '', '2014-11-06 14:03:58', '2014-11-06 14:03:58', '', 0, 'http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/?p=411', 0, 'post', '', 0),
