(327, 3, '2014-09-28 02:38:04', '2014-09-28 01:38:04', '<a href="http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/dukey1.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-82" style="border: 1px solid black; margin: 10px;" src="http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/dukey1.jpg" alt="dukey" width="269" height="146" /></a>On 25th August 2013 we are doing a calendar photoshoot for our 2014 Greyhound Rescue calendar in aid of ''The Rescue Duke Appeal''!\r\nThanks to the boys at Kennings Building Supplies Ltd/eDecks &amp; some local girls who have kindly donated their bodies to raise money and awareness for our charity.\r\nWe would like to thank Kennings Building Supplies Ltd/eDecks staff who are taking part in the calendar and Nigel and Michaela Kenning for the use of a few tools.\r\nNo way to talk about their staff I know but I am sure it will be a lot of fun and I can confirm that Karen Schultz, much to her horror is also appearing in the calendar and I can assure you, she will be removing some items of clothing. However, I have been told she would have to have her wellies surgically removed so due to timescales, they may have to stay on!\r\nPlease watch out for more updates on the calendar in the next few days.\r\n\r\nThe Calendars are now on sale at £5.99 plus postage (no more than £1.00).\r\n\r\nPlease look at our lastest news content to see more on calendars.\r\n\r\nThank you\r\nDawn', 'Calender Photoshoot!', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '1-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-28 02:38:04', '2014-09-28 01:38:04', '', 1, 'http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/1-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(329, 2, '2010-09-28 02:52:03', '2010-09-28 01:52:03', '[vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]Greyhound Rescue would like to give a big thank you to all the trustees of Greyhound Compassion. Not only have they contributed £4000 to complete our new kennel extension but they are helping with other important items for our rescues, bedding, food, potential homes and even toys.\r\n\r\nTheir support towards this rescue is very much valued, also their kindness in sponsoring Duke. We look forward to working together in the future as it is a big boost for the dogs in our care to know we have people that will help to support our work.\r\n\r\nThe photo across is Greyhound Compassion presenting the £4000 cheque to two of our trustees for the continuing work of our charity.\r\n\r\nA big thankyou from all of us.\r\n\r\nMore information about Greyhound Compassion can be found on their website:\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.greyhoundcompassion.com/" target="_blank">Greyhound Compassion</a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="330" alignment="right" border_color="grey" img_link_target="_self" img_size="large"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'A big thankyou to Greyhound Compassion', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'a-big-thankyou-to-greyhound-compassion', '', '', '2014-09-28 03:39:07', '2014-09-28 02:39:07', '', 0, 'http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/?p=329', 0, 'post', '', 0);
