(466, 4, '2014-12-30 17:39:38', '2014-12-30 17:39:38', '[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]Owners have raced greyhounds for many years and race goers see them muzzled, chasing a make believe hare. The public gain a lot of excitement from the spectacle and gamble thousands of pounds on their performance. When they have finished their usual track life, either because they are too old, injured, or just not fast enough, they are disposed of. The lucky ones end up in Greyhound Rescue for re-homing as family pets.\r\n\r\nThe problem they then have is overcoming the public''s image of the breed. It is generally thought that they need to be kept muzzled, are dangerous around children and need lots of exercise.\r\n\r\nAs with all breeds each greyhound has it''s own temperament but in general greyhounds are extremely lazy, spending most of their time either flat on their backs, with their legs in the air, or sprawled out in their bed fast asleep. Most only need two walks a day and the freedom of an enclosed back garden. They love a cuddle and in particular like their bellies rubbed.\r\n\r\nA greyhound sees a lot further than a human being and if they see something in the distance they will set off to chase it, so it is wise to keep them on a lead at all times when walking them, but they saunter along at a genteel pace, giving the owners a steady walk.\r\n\r\nIn general a Greyhound is one of the most loving pets to own and will give many years of love and friendship to it''s lucky owner.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/1"][vc_cta_button call_text="If you are interested in learning more about greyhounds, please ask us anything and we''ll do our best to help. " title="Get In Touch" target="_self" color="btn-primary" icon="wpb_arrow" size="wpb_regularsize" position="cta_align_right"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'About Greyhounds', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '89-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-12-30 17:39:38', '2014-12-30 17:39:38', '', 89, 'http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/89-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(469, 2, '2015-01-15 13:38:06', '2015-01-15 13:38:06', '[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]<strong>Wolfie’s Breeze Block Appeal</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Greyhound Rescue have planned to build an extension to help other people when they find it impossible to contemplate a holiday because they simply do not want their pets to be put in a kennel environment.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>So, this extension will give peoples pets a home from home environment, with live in humans to see to their every needs, whilst their owners can go and enjoy their well earned holiday with peace of mind that their pets are in good hands.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>This decision was also brought forward because of unforeseen circumstances of owners needing to go into hospital for a length a time and we have been in the position of having to put their pets into the kennels. This has been quite upsetting in the past and distressing for the pets.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>We have thought long and hard about this and how we can help owners and their pets and with this in mind, we have decided to run a breeze block appeal to help with the funding of our project.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>This will be called, <em>‘Wolfie’s Breeze Block Appeal’</em>. This is in memory of our beautiful blue girl Wolfie who we lost late last year at the grand young age of 22.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Wolfie was an amazing greyhound and was at the rescue for 20 years. We will be sharing her story and pictures throughout the appeal.</strong>\r\n\r\n<em><strong>If you</strong> <strong>would like to buy a breeze block to help raise funds for Wolfies Appeal these are £2.00 per block  and you can donate online through our paypal donate button on our website.</strong></em>\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Thank you.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Karen Schultz (&amp; Wolfie) X</strong>\r\n\r\n<a class="iol_imc"><img class="mainImage" src="http://sabercatfootball.com/wp-content/blogs.dir/82/files/2011/06/bricks-e1315592056613.gif" alt="" /></a>\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'WOLFIE''S BREEZE BLOCK APPEAL', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'wolfies-breeze-block-appeal', '', '', '2015-02-01 13:25:32', '2015-02-01 13:25:32', '', 0, 'http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/?page_id=469', 0, 'page', '', 0);
