(511, 2, '2015-02-01 18:09:49', '2015-02-01 18:09:49', '[vc_row][vc_column width="1/1"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h1 style="text-align: center;">In Memorium</h1>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="213" alignment="center" img_link_target="_self" img_size="full"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h3>Kenny &amp; Archie</h3>\r\nIt is with such massive heartache to let our rescue friends and sponsors know that we have had to say goodbye to 2 of our most precious boys.\r\nKenny &amp; Archie both fell asleep this morning 8th August 2014 at the age of 19.\r\nThey had been with Karen here at the rescue for over 15 years as they could not be rehomed due to the horrific traumas they had suffered in their racing days.\r\nBoth Kenny &amp; Archie were brilliant dogs and gentle, brave boys until the end.\r\nWe will miss you always boys and the kennels will never be the same without you. xxxxx\r\n\r\nAll our love forever\r\nKaren &amp; Dawn[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="214" alignment="center" img_link_target="_self" img_size="full"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h3>Duke</h3>\r\nIt is with sadness and regret that we have to announce the loss of Duke who sadly passed away on Monday 25th March 2013.\r\nTo all his friends and the people who loved him\r\nThose who knew him so well and those who he made laugh\r\nAll the hearts he touched with his brave and determined willpower\r\nNever complaining about anything, even though he was not only blind but he had so many other problems.\r\nHis character of fun and joy won everyone’s affection, who were lucky enough to meet him.\r\nFor this beautiful black greyhound''s soul, so precious to us, so special and loving.\r\nHe has now left us, so quickly and suddenly, and broken so many hearts.\r\nWe have lost a dear friend in you, young man and a hole in our lives.\r\n\r\nThere will never be another ‘Duke’ X\r\n\r\nKaren Schultz…. (Duke’s mum).[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_single_image image="64" border_color="grey" img_link_target="_self"][/vc_column][vc_column width="3/4"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h3>Wolfie</h3>\r\nIt is with great sadness that we have to tell you that we have now lost wolfie. She passed away after a short illness and has left a massive hole in our lives. She was 22 years old though had the body and energy of a puppy, right until the end.\r\n\r\nWolfie had the most horrendous start to her life and it took Karen some time to win Wolfie round as she was so terrified of everyone. I, as well as everyone who met ''The Wolf'' will miss her forever. She was one of a kind and she was a kind girl. Patch and West have lost their sister and I know the Wolf missed Queenie her Bengal friend who we lost a few months ago. She has now joined her. Whitey, the cat and Caster the new Bengal will also miss her. She adored the cats as they did her.\r\n\r\nLove always our Angel. xxxxx\r\n\r\nMummy and Dawn\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI am Wolfie. I am a beautiful tiny blue greyhound who loves to sing! I am an old lady and my singing voice is not what it used to be...or so Patch tells me.\r\n\r\nMe &amp; Patch are best of friends though and love to cuddle up together on a night.\r\n\r\nMy mum Karen adores my singing as I do hers! (NOT)! I often pretend to not hear mum when she calls me in from the garden. She thinks my sight &amp; hearing is going as I am so old but I still enjoy my food and a good old dance around the kitchen table with Queenie the house cat.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/1"][vc_single_image image="442" border_color="grey" img_link_target="_self"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>Danny</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">It is difficult to truly describe Danny. By the time we lost him, at the age of 9yrs old he was known as our toothless, tail-less, hairless, brainless wonder! Before that he had many other names, an anaconda on springs, commander Dan Dan and most of all, our gorgeous Danny boy.  He was a true clown and would make you smile and laugh whenever anything wasn''t so great.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">In 2010 I was lucky enough to get Danny from Karen and after five fabulous years with him, on 28 September 2014 he made the decision to leave us.  We had no choice, just as he had had no choice 3 months earlier when his beloved Binty girl had left.  He is now back with her, curled up together as they always were, happy.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Danny, we miss you every day.  Our newbies, whilst very cute and lovely are not, and we do not want them to be you but we miss you, so much.  Sleep well gorgeous boy. All our love, Mummy Ruth and Mummy Lel xxx</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'In Memorium ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '212-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-02-01 18:09:49', '2015-02-01 18:09:49', '', 212, 'http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/212-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(512, 2, '2015-02-01 18:14:37', '2015-02-01 18:14:37', '[vc_row][vc_column width="1/1"][vc_column_text]We are a charity based in Lincolnshire and Yorkshire and have spent over 35 years caring for and helping re-home these kind, gentle, affectionate and appreciative breed.[/vc_column_text][vc_separator][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/4"][service_block title="Adopt" target="_self" icon="icon-heart-1" href="http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/meet-the-dogs/"]If you have a loving home and are ready for the love a greyhound will give, please get in touch.[/service_block][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][service_block title="Sponsor" icon="icon-heart-1" href="http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/meet-the-dogs/" target="_self"]If you can''t give a dog a home but want to help, you can sponsor one of our dogs - they''ll love you for it![/service_block][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][service_block title="Donate" icon="icon-heart-1" target="_blank" href="https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr?cmd=_s-xclick&amp;hosted_button_id=5E7JL56V28B2C"]If you just want to help retired and abandoned greyhounds with a donation, you can do that with paypal. Thanks![/service_block][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][service_block title="Shop" icon="icon-basket-1" target="_self" href="http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/shop/"]We have calendars and other items for sale in the on-line shop. All proceeds go straight to the welfare of the dogs.[/service_block][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/1"][vc_column_text]Many of you will know the story of our chairpersons first sighting of two greyhounds, she was aged ten, yet the elegance and beauty of the breed lived with her until the age of 23 when she was able to adopt a greyhound of her own. From there a great passion for these noble gentle dogs was built and so the rescue sanctuary began.\r\n\r\nLooking back over the years we have helped greyhounds from many different circumstances. There has been happiness, frustration, sadness and all those other emotions running riot that form part of running an animal sanctuary, but most of all there has been the feeling of great satisfaction when a greyhound has been re-homed into a loving family life, a life that enables them to build their own character, to be an individual and at last find themselves belonging and loved by someone special.\r\n\r\nGreyhounds are great characters and dare we say it, have a great sense of humour. (We''re just waiting for scientists to finally catch up with what all Greyhound owners already know!)[/vc_column_text][spacer height="25"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2" el_class="Wolfie''s Block Appeal"][velocity_headline title="Sponsor a Dog" target="_self"][vc_column_text]<img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-173" src="http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/tommycrop_tall-217x300.jpg" alt="tommycrop_tall" width="217" height="300" />In addition to rehoming greyhounds, we also offer sponsorships.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, some of the dogs that are with us have suffered severe trauma and will probably never be able to be re-homed.\r\n\r\nHowever, you can help by sponsoring.\r\n\r\nWe will keep you updated with photographs, newsletters and a Christmas card! Please see how you can sponsor a dog in the information section.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][velocity_headline title="Sponsor a Cat. (Yes, really!)" target="_self"][vc_column_text]<img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-171" src="http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/2014site/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Mr_Castor-225x300.jpg" alt="Mr_Castor" width="225" height="300" />Having over the last couple of years, (and somewhat surprisingly) found ourselves a meeting place for stray cats, we now have a number of permanent residents that may not at first seem congruent with a Greyhound Rescue, but we never turn a homeless animal away.\r\nWe now have a dozen cats that could use your help via sponsorship or donation and we hope soon, to help them into new homes.\r\nThe chap to the left goes by the name of Mr Castor and was a great friend of our now departed beautiful girl Wolfie.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '12-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-02-01 18:14:37', '2015-02-01 18:14:37', '', 12, 'http://www.greyhoundrescue.org.uk/12-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
